   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE TO OVERCOME PERSECUTION, WORLDLINESS, AND SPIRITUAL DEATH Scripture Reading: Rev 2:8-13, 17b; 3:1-5 OUTLINE To overcome persecution, comprising tribulation, poverty, trial, imprisonment, and the slander of the deformed religion of Satan Rev 2:9-10a: By being faithful unto death, not loving the soul-life 2:10b; 12:11b.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The reward: To receive the crown of life 2:10c.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Not to be hurt by the second death 2:11.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To overcome worldliness: In a church that is affiliated with the world, where Satan administrates on his throne and dwells for his possession 2:13.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To overcome such worldliness is to hold fast the name of the Lord and not deny the faith concerning the Lord 2:13.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The reward 2:17b: To be given to eat of the hidden manna Christ for nourishment .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To be given a white stone for the building in the Body of Christ , upon which a new name is written, which no one knows except he who receives it.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To overcome spiritual death: In a church having a name that it is living and yet being dead, with nothing completed before God 3:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To overcome spiritual death is to be watchful and establish the things of life, which are about to die, and not to be defiled with the stain of spiritual death 3:2, 4.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The reward: Not to miss the Lord in His coming secretly as a thief 3:3b.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To be clothed in white signifying being justified and approved by the Lord in the purity of life and walk with the Lord 3:4-5a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To have his name never erased out of the book of life but confessed by the Lord before His Father and His Father's angels 3:5b.</S>
   </TEXT>
